    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab><note>Il principe Arechi II offre al monastero di S. Sofia di Benevento (prosegue
                        l'elenco iniziato con il doc. 3535):</note></ab> <ab>(…) [17] Concessimus et iam dicto <orgName ref="#juridical_persons/85"
                            key="#Curtes #Landed_possessions #Wine #Property_of_persons_without_heirs #Property_of_criminals/political_traitors #Monasteries #Slave"
                                ><rs
                                key="#Houses #Curtes #Landed_possessions #Wine #Monasteries #Slave"
                                >monasterio</rs> Sancte Sophię</orgName> substantiam que fuit <name
                            ref="Gaiderissius">Gayderissi</name> filius <name ref="Iohannes"
                            >Iohannis</name>, quam legibus per culpam suam perdidit eo quod contra
                        animam nostram consiliatus est et furatus est nobis decem milia solidos de
                        quibus nec unu conparuit, et pro his duobus perfidis offensis omnis eius <rs
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Object #Redistributive #Confiscation #Property_of_criminals/political_traitors"
                            >substantia</rs> ad nostre potestatis manum pervenit, ideo dum legibus
                        ad nos pertenuisse predicto monasterio Sancte Sophię in integrum concessi
                        possidendum, <rs
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Object #Redistributive #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches #Property_of_criminals/political_traitors"
                                ><rs key="#Slave">servos et ancillas</rs>, universas <rs
                                key="#Curtes">cortes</rs>, <rs key="#Houses">casas</rs>, <rs
                                key="#Landed_possessions">campos</rs>, <rs key="#Wine">vineas</rs>,
                                <rs key="#Landed_possessions">territoria</rs>, <rs
                                key="#Landed_possessions">silvas</rs>, <rs key="#Landed_possessions"
                                >prata</rs>, mobilia et inmobilia</rs> queque habere nominato
                        Gayderissi visus fuit; seu et substantiam <name ref="Ursus">Ursi</name>
                        germano eius qui cum ipso similiter contra nostra anima est consiliatus, et
                        pro alia culpa quod uxorem suam nomine <name ref="Simplicia"
                            >Simplicia</name> quem <rs key="#Tuitio/bannum/mundeburdium">in mundio
                            nostri palatii</rs> fuit sine culpa occidere visus est, unde pro ipsa
                        culpa debuit componere secundum legem solidos mille duocentos, et <rs
                            key="#Property_of_criminals/political_traitors">propter eius iniquum
                            consilium</rs> ideoque et <rs key="#Property_of_persons_without_heirs"
                            >sine heredes mortuus</rs> est omnis <rs
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Object #Redistributive #Inflow #Confiscation"
                            >eius substantia legibus ad nostra devenit potestate</rs>, nostra vero
                        potestas omnia in integrum eius <rs
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Object #Redistributive #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >substantię</rs> quantum ipse Ursus possidere visus fuit in monasterio
                        Sancte Sophie concessimus possidendum. (…)</ab>
                </div>
            </div>
